We analyzed the data and annotations for the 111,743 wells (Ts = 2, N = 72) in the Zhang et al., 2009 screen [12]. Fits for which the R2 < 0.80 were discarded. The natural logarithm of the amplitude was used, since it more closely resembled a normal distribution and was on a similar scale to the damping rate. Plate to plate variation, as shown in S3 Fig, was more severe than variation on a well-to-well basis, S4 Fig. Parameters were therefore normalized on a plate-by-plate basis using a robust z-score [30]:
